        <div class="craft__content">
          <p class="eyebrow">From Seed to Smoke</p>
          <h2 class="section-heading craft__heading" id="craft-heading">The Craft of Three Generations</h2>
          <div class="gold-rule" role="presentation"></div>
          <p class="craft__lede">
            From leaves cured in the Nicaraguan sun to the band that seals every
            finished cigar, nothing at Pita is rushed and nothing is delegated
            to a machine.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="craft__quote">
            <p>&ldquo;His goal was simple: obtain the finest tobacco there is.&rdquo;</p>
            <cite>The standard set by Arnaldo Laurencio, 1968</cite>
          </blockquote>
          <ol class="craft__steps">
            <li class="craft__step">
              <span class="craft__step-number" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="craft__step-title">Hand-Selected Leaf</h3>
                <p class="craft__step-body">Every leaf is personally inspected by our master blenders, sourced from twelve tobacco-growing regions worldwide.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="craft__step">
              <span class="craft__step-number" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="craft__step-title">Slow-Cured &amp; Aged</h3>
                <p class="craft__step-body">Wrappers ferment for a minimum of 18 months, and every blend rests in Spanish cedar for at least three years.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="craft__step">
              <span class="craft__step-number" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="craft__step-title">Rolled by Masters</h3>
                <p class="craft__step-body">No shortcuts, no machines. Every cigar passes a certified master roller and has earned 40+ ratings of 93 points or higher.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="craft__collage" role="group" aria-label="Photos of the Flor de Pita curing barn, rolling table, and finished cigars">
